# This directory contains scripts to create a QSPI tarball and flash QSPI to Jetson.

	README                                    <-- This file
	host_flash_qspi.sh                        <-- Final host running script included in tarball
	kernel_flash_qspi.sh                      <-- Script included in downloaded rcm-boot invoked initrd to flash Jetson's QSPI
	generate_qspi_for_flash.sh                <-- Script to build QSPI tarball for Jetson's flash

# Prerequisites:
	- x86-64 Linux build machine
	- NVIDIA sample file system or user provided root file system


# Build the QSPI tarball

This section explains how to build a QSPI image and subsequent tarball. These steps must be completed
using an x86-64 linux build machine. The usb connection to Jetson is not required for this process.

1. Download one of the following packages:
	- customer_release.tbz2
	- Jetson_Linux_<VERSION>_aarch64.tbz2

2. Install the BSP package.

3. After you installed customer_release.tbz2 or Jetson_Linux_<VERSION>_aarch64.tbz2:
	a. Install NVIDIA Orin/Thor sample file system to Linux_for_Tegra/rootfs.
	b. Go to the Linux_for_Tegra directory
	c. Choose the online or offline mode to generate the QSPI image:
		Online mode - Put the board into recovery mode, then issue the command:
		$ sudo ./tools/qspi_flash/generate_qspi_for_flash.sh <board-name>
		Offline mode:
		$ sudo BOARDID=<BOARDID> FAB=<FAB> BOARDSKU=<BOARDSKU> CHIP_SKU="00:00:00:xx" ./tools/qspi_flash/generate_qspi_for_flash.sh <board-name>

		The script will create a tarball in
			generic_release_aarch64/Linux_for_Tegra/host_tegraflash_<VERSION>.tbz2


# Flash the Jetson's QSPI image from host

This section explains run the script to flash the Jetson's QSPI flash memory.

1. Untar the tarball
	$ tar -xvf host_tegraflash_<VERSION>.tbz2

2. Flash the Jetson's QSPI image from the host
	Option 1. User manually put the board into recovery mode:
		$ sudo hostflash/host_flash_qspi.sh
	Option 2. Use the boardctl tool in BSP to put the board into recovery mode:
		$ cd Linux_for_Tegra
		$ sudo ./hostflash/host_flash_qspi.sh -b


# Create the customized QSPI tarball

This section describes how to create a customized QSPI tarball for different board configurations.

The usage for the generate_qspi_for_flash.sh script is:
	Usage: <env-var> generate_qspi_for_flash.sh [-u <PKC key file>] [-v <SBK key file>] [-p <options>] [-f <flash-mode>] <board-name>

To see more details on specifying board configurations and examples, run the following command:
	$ sudo ./tools/qspi_flash/generate_qspi_for_flash.sh -h


Note:
1. Replace <VERSION> with the actual version number of the Jetson release(for example, R36.4.0).
